                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18221204-51-off275 t18221204-51-crimeloc278"></join>. The prisoner was in the tap-room on the 18th of November - he asked for a lodging, and was told he could not have one. He called for half a pint of beer - I saw him take up my hat, which was on the seat, and wrapt it up in a cloth. I stopped him, and asked what he wanted with it - he said he was not going to take it away. I had put my apron on the bench, and the landlady told me to feel in his pockets, and I found my apron there. I turned him out, and the watchman soon after brought him back.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18221204-51-person449">
